-- HIGHLIGHTS-BoE's Carney speaks on financial policy in parliament
-- 
-- Wed Jan 15, 2014 09:36AM EST
-- None



LONDON, Jan 15 (Reuters) - Bank of England Governor Mark Carney and other members of the Bank's Financial Policy Committee appeared before the Treasury Select Committee in Britain's parliament on Wednesday.

Highlights of their comments are below.  CARNEY ON BANK SIZE  "Just breaking up an institution doesn't necessarily create a viable or more intensive competitive structure."  CARNEY, ASKED IF HE AGREES THAT CRUDE BONUS CAP IS NOT BEST WAY TO CONTROL PAY:  "Absolutely."